  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6571.48 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6575, dealers are currently long gamma and likely providing modest buying support after the recent wall break event, though their hedging flow is minimal in this tight range. The massive +70.1B gamma wall at 6580 will trigger significant dealer selling pressure on any rally above 6575, creating a strong ceiling effect that should cap upside momentum and drive mean reversion back toward 6570-6575. Watch for increased volatility compression as we approach the 6580 wall, with dealers expected to aggressively sell rallies above 6575 and provide stabilizing bids on any dips toward the 6570 support level.",
